    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It is not easy to provide you our software. \r\n\r\nI found a reason, why we received this GRPC_CALL_ERROR_TOO_MANY_OPERATIONS.\r\nThe \"grpcStreamer->writesDone()\" can not be invoked, if a Write() is still pending. \r\n\r\nBut the main issue remains: The grpc code is full of abort() invocations. Our process crashed due to this all the time and finding this \"too_many_operations\" was a lot of work inclusive changing the grpc code.\r\nAnd knowing that the grpc lib is full of abort() invocations and not knowing when and how these might trigger results in a bad feeling. So why is it full of abort() invocations?"
  },
