    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So you have found your problem on your end, which was you using our API incorrectly, and I consider this matter resolved.\r\n\r\nAs a *server* code, the asserts in it are meant to protect you from two sorts of situations:\r\n\r\n-) you using the API incorrectly, which could lead to various security issues such as leaking information to the outside world or allowing for remote execution exploits.\r\n-) us having a corner case situation that we never thought was possible, which could also lead to various security issues such as leaking information or allowing remote execution.\r\n\r\nIn both cases, this is a \"better safe than sorry\" principle of precaution. The normal usage of the API, including flaky network conditions, invalid client requests, or any other external factors, should not trigger any assert."
